text: Leon Moore (8 February 1871 - 11 September 1934) was an Australian cricketer. He played eleven first-class matches for New South Wales between 1892/93 and 1894/95. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1871 births Category:1934 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers
title: Leon Moore
